    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nLet's take this one step at a time! Click the arrow to expand the step when you're ready.\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">1. Add a <code>Painter</code> parameter to the functions</span>]\r\nLook at the `take_three_paint()` and `paint_then_move()` functions near the top of the code.\r\n\r\nBoth functions are missing a parameter. Add `this_painter` inside the parentheses of each function so they know which `Painter` to use.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">2. Update both functions to use the parameter</span>]\r\nInside the functions, update the code so it uses `this_painter` instead of `sally` and `helen`.\r\n\r\nThis will allow the same functions to work with any `Painter` object.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">3. Call the functions with <code>sally</code> as the argument</span>]\r\nScroll down and find the `TODO`s for calling the functions with `sally`.\r\n\r\nReplace the existing calls or lines of code with a call to your function using `sally` as the argument.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n:::details [<span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">4. Call the functions with <code>helen</code> as the argument</span>]\r\n\r\nNow find the `TODO`s for calling the functions with `helen`.\r\n\r\nReplace the three `take_paint()` lines with a single call to `take_three_paint(helen)`.\r\n\r\nAlso update the call to `paint_then_move()` so it uses `helen` as the argument.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<span></span>\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/c5a2adc6ae7248b0d1d81ca7554dcc70-choiceB.gif)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nTo make your function flexible, use a parameter like `this_painter` so the function works with any `Painter` you choose.\r\n\r\n**Example:**\r\n\r\n```\r\ndef paint_line(this_painter):\r\n  this_painter.take_paint()\r\n  this_painter.paint(\"white\")\r\n  this_painter.move()\r\n\r\npaint_line(south_side_painter)\r\n```",
